18 0 obj
<< /Length 1353 >>
stream
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 712.0 Td (10 CALM-DOWN STRATEGIES \(For Kids\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 690.0 Td (\(Print as cards, let child CHOOSE which one to try\)) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 666.2 Td (1. Belly Breathing: Breathe in like smelling a flower, out like blowing a candle. 5 times.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 642.4 Td (2. Tight Squeeze Hug: Ask: 'Can I give you a tight squeeze?' or let them hug a stuffed) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 628.4 Td (animal.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 604.6 Td (  3. Stomp It Out: Stomp feet 10 times. Get the angry energy OUT through your feet.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 580.8 Td (  4. Count to 10: Count slowly together. Whisper by the time you reach 10.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 557.0 Td (  5. Safe Space: Go to a designated 'calm corner' with pillows and soft things.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 533.2 Td (  6. Ice Cube Hold: Hold an ice cube until it melts. The sensation redirects the brain.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 509.4 Td (  7. Draw Your Feelings: Give paper and crayons. 'Draw how big your feeling is.') Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 485.6 Td (  8. Body Shake: Shake hands, arms, legs, whole body for 30 seconds. Then freeze.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 461.8 Td (  9. Name 5 Things: 5 things you can see, 4 you can hear, 3 you can touch...) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 438.0 Td (  10. Blow Bubbles: Blowing = controlled breathing. Watching = calming. Win-win.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
